5000|$|Dianne Perry Vanderlip, Curator, Modern and Contemporary Art, Denver Art Museum, knew Kirkland {{during the}} last three years of his life and was co-curator <b>of</b> <b>the</b> Vance Kirkland FIFTY YEARS retrospective. She noted: “...each of these periods, of course, has been tied {{together}} with a primary interest <b>of</b> communicating <b>the</b> <b>human</b> <b>spirit’s</b> adventure through time. Obviously, though he titles these paintings with space age titles—Nebula Near Saturn and that kind of thing—these are not science fiction paintings; these are paintings about <b>the</b> adventure <b>of</b> <b>the</b> <b>human</b> spirit.” ...|$|R
